Name.BusinessNameLine1: ALUMNI ASSOCIATION OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: ITS PURPOSE IS TO PROVIDE A TWO-WAY COMMUNICATION LINK BETWEEN KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY AND ITS ALUMNI AND FRIENDS.
IRS990.MissionDescription: PROVIDE ACTIVITIES SPECIFICALLY DIRECTED TO THE WELFARE OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY, TO MAINTAIN THE INTEREST OF PAST FORMER STUDENTS AND ALL GRADUATE ALUMNI OF THE UNIVERSITY AND TO CAUSE THEM TO BE RESPONSIVE TO THE PROGRAM NEEDS OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY.
IRS990.Description: ALUMNI ACTIVITIES/EVENT OPPORTUNITIES - THE PURPOSE OF THIS PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE INFORMATIONAL AND SOCIAL ACTIVITIES, COMMUNICATIONS AND BENEFITS TO MAINTAIN AND DEVELOP PURPOSFUL RELATIONSHIPS WITH ALUMNI AND PROMOTE ACQUAINTANCES AMOUNG GRADUATES OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY.

Activity2.Description: STUDENT ENROLLMENT - THIS PROGRAM PROVIDES ACTIVITIES, SCHOLARSHIPS AND SERVICES TO INCREASE INTEREST AND INVOLVEMENT IN BOTH PROSPECTIVE STUDENTS TO ATTEND KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY AND CURRENT ENROLLED STUDENTS FOR RETENTION.

Activity3.Description: ALUMNI RECORDS - THE ALUMNI ASSOCIATION OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY MAINTAINS AND UPDATES DEMOGRAPHICAL INFOMATION ON MORE THAN 250,000 KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY GRADUATES, FORMER STUDENTS, AND FRIENDS OF THE UNIVERSITY. THROUGH THE EFFORTS OF THE ALUMNI RECORDS PROGRAM, A 90% ADDRESSABLE MAILING LIST IS MAINTAINED WHICH ALLOWS THE ASSOCIATION TO ACHIEVE ITS EXEMPT PURPOSE.

ActivityOther.Description: PUBLICATIONS - THE AWARD-WINING K-STATER MAGAZINE IS DISTRIBUTED FIVE TIMES A YEAR TO MORE THAN 39,000 ALUMNI MEMBERS, ELEMENTARY AND SECONDARY SCHOOLS, AND LIBARIES. THIS PERIODICAL INFORMS ALUMNI, PROSPECTIVE STUDENTS, AND INTERESTED CONSTITUENT GROUPS OF THE ACTIVITIES OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY AND ITS ALUMNI.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Intended Use of Endowment Funds:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE BEING HELD TO PROVIDE SCHOLARSHIPS FOR BOTH INCOMING STUDENTS AND CURRENT ENROLLED STUDENTS OF KANSAS STATE UNIVERSITY. ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE ALSO HELD TO SUPPLEMENT ALUMNI ASSOCIATION STUDENT AMBASSADOR PROGRAMS AND ALUMNI CENTER OPERATIONAL COSTS.
Part XII line 2d These amounts are direct costs which were presented as expense on the financial statements and offset against revenue on the tax return

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 6
Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 7a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION VOTE TO RATIFY THE GOVERNING BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR THE ASSOCIATION. INDIVIDUALS ARE MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION THROUGH PAYMENT OF MEMBERSHIP DUES.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE DESIGNEES SHALL RECEIVE A COPY OF THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO SUBMISSION OF THE FORM TO THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AND THE ASSOCIATION SHALL NOT FILE THE FORM 990 UNTIL ALL THE DESIGNEE MEMBERS HAVE REVIEWED THE COMPLETED FORM 990.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ALL POSSIBLE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST DISCLOSED ANNUALLY ARE REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. ALL NEW VENDORS ARE REVIEWED FOR POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST PARTIES OR RELATIONSHIPS BEFORE BEING APPROVED TO CONDUCT BUSINESS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ASSOCIATION'S EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION PROGRAM BY AUTHORIZATION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS ADMINISTERED BY A COMPENSATION COMMITTEE THAT IS RESPONSIBLE FOR ESTABLISHING AND MAINTAINING A COMPETITIVE PROGRAM FOR THE PRESIDENT OF THE ASSOCIATION. THE COMMITTEE USES COMPARABILITY DATA INCLUDING MARKET SURVEYS, CONSULTANTS AND SURVEYS OR PEER GROUP ASSOCIATIONS AND FORM 990'S OF SIMILAR NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS. COMPENSATION IS BASED ON THE MARKET FOR EXPERIENCE, PERFORMANCE AND BUSINESS NEED TO ATTRACT AND RETAIN QUALIFIED INDIVIDUALS. THE BOARD AUTHORIZES THE PRESIDENT TO ESTABLISH AND SET PAY RANGES, CLASSIFICATION ASSIGNMENTS AND POLICIES FOR PROMOTION, DEMOTION AND RECLASSIFICATION FOR ALL OTHER STAFF INCLUDING OTHER KEY OFFICERS OF THE ASSOCIATION. ALL STAFF ARE REVIEWED WITH WRITTEN DOCUMENTATION ANNUALLY AND ANY RECOMMENDED CHANGES ARE INCORPORATED INTO THE BUDGET TO BE APPROVED BY THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS EACH YEAR.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 18
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE IRS FORM 990 AND FORM 1023 ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST. COPIES WILL BE PROVIDED IMMEDIATELY IN THE CASE OF IN-PERSON REQUESTS. REQUESTS RECEIVED BY WRITTEN, PHONE, FAX OR E-MAIL MEANS WILL BE SENT BY DIRECT MAIL.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST ARE COPIES OF THE ASSOCIATION'S ANNUAL REPORT AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. COPIES WILL BE PROVIDED IMMEDIATELY IN THE CASE OF IN-PERSON REQUESTS. REQUESTS RECEIVED BY WRITTEN, PHONE, FAX OR E-MAIL MEANS WILL BE SENT BY DIRECT MAIL.
